onics\". Archived from the original on September 8, 2016. Retrieved September 11, 2023.\n  4. ^ Howley, Kerry (7 July 2010). \"Until Cryonics Do Us Part\". The New York Times Magazine. Archived from the original on 16 May 2016. Retrieved 21 May 2022.\n  5. ^ Haines, Lester (2007-10-23). \"Paris Hilton heads for the cryogenic freezer\". The Register. Retrieved 2024-02-02.\n  6. ^ Philipkoski, Kristen (2002-11-18). \"Ray Kurzweil's Plan: Never Die\". Wired. Archived from the original on 2023-02-02. Retrieved January 11, 2021.\n  7. ^ \"Seth MacFarlane On Cryonics\". Ora TV. 2012-07-12. Archived from the original on 2021-01-23. Retrieved January 11, 2021.\n  8. ^ Merkle, Ralph. \"Cryonics\". Archived from the original on August 16, 2005. Retrieved January 12, 2021.\n  9. ^ Goodwin, John (28 November 2021). \"Cryonics: Putting your future plans for life on ice\". CBS Sunday Morning. CBS News. Archived from the original on 15 November 2022. Retrieved 21 May 2022.\n  10. ^ Pearce, David. \"Quora Answers 2015 - 2022 by David Pearce\". The Hedonistic Imperative. Archived from the original on January 16, 2022.\n  11. ^ \"Martine Rothblatt: My daughter, my wife, our robot, and the quest for immortality\". Archived from the original on October 19, 2023. Retrieved September 11, 2023.\n  12. ^ \"V&A \u00b7 Project focus | Cryonics: who wants to live forever?\". Victoria and Albert Museum. Archived from the original on 2022-12-06. Retrieved 2020-05-11.\n  13. ^ Antonio Regalado (January 21, 2006). \"A Cold Calculus Leads Cryonauts To Put Assets on Ice With Bodies Frozen, They Hope to Return Richer; Dr. Thorp Is Buying Long\". The Wall Street Journal. Archived from the original on November 12, 2022. Retrieved January 22, 2021.\n  14. ^ Alexander, Brian. \"Don't Die, Stay Pretty\". Archived from the original on December 15, 2014. Retrieved September 11, 2023.\n  15. ^ Yudkowsky, Eliezer. \"You Only Live Twice\". LessWrong. Archived from the original on 23 March 2023. Retrieved 21 M